Update react-day-picker to version 8.10.1
Downgrades react-day-picker from version 9.7.0 to 8.10.1 to ensure compatibility with existing dependencies.
Removes unused dependencies from package-lock.json, streamlining the package management and reducing potential conflicts.

Adds vessel fetching functionality and code cleanup
Introduces a new function to fetch all vessels dynamically based on city data.
Refactors existing code for improved readability by removing unnecessary line breaks and ensuring consistent formatting.
Enhances error handling for vessel imports and improves logging messages for better debugging.
This update streamlines the vessel management process within the application.

Adds new cuisine types to Restaurant type definition
Introduces "Asian" and "Southern" as additional cuisine options in the Restaurant type.
This enhancement expands the variety of restaurant classifications, improving data representation and flexibility in the application.

Refactors Amsterdam cruise data structure for consistency
Enhances the data structure of Amsterdam cruise details by standardizing formatting and improving readability.
These changes include consistent use of object property formatting, ensuring clear separation of information. This refactoring aims to facilitate easier maintenance and future updates.
No functional changes were made to the cruise details or logic.

Refactors import statements and formatting in calendar and form components
Standardizes import statements by removing unnecessary semicolons and ensuring consistent formatting across calendar and form components.
This change improves code readability and maintains a uniform coding style throughout the project.

Fixes formatting inconsistencies in query strings
Addresses minor formatting issues by ensuring consistent trailing commas in function arguments.
This change enhances code readability and maintains a uniform style throughout the file.

Refactors destination search and sorting logic
Improves the destination filtering by simplifying the search criteria to directly access properties.
Updates sorting logic to consistently use "country" and "city" for better clarity.
Enhances the UI interaction by streamlining the click handlers for routing, ensuring a more efficient navigation experience.

Removes unused tag list from cruise categories
Eliminates the display of tags in the cruise categories section to streamline the user interface.
This change enhances readability by focusing on key information without unnecessary elements.

Fixes syntax issues in booking confirmation and trip pages
Corrects trailing commas in multiple function calls and object initializations to ensure consistent syntax throughout the booking confirmation and trip pages.
Enhances code readability and maintains uniformity in style without altering any functionality.

Refactors vessel data handling with async fetching
Implements asynchronous fetching of vessel data from an API, improving data management and performance.
Replaces hardcoded vessel data with dynamic API data, groups vessels by type, and initializes pagination state accordingly.
Enhances the user interface by displaying the correct number of vessels and improving overall application responsiveness.

Fix formatting issues in kebabToCamelCase functions
Corrects trailing commas in `kebabToCamelCase` function calls and several other locations to ensure consistent code formatting.
Improves readability and maintains coding standards across various files related to city cruise and vessel data generation.
No functional changes were made; this is purely a formatting update.

Fixes regex patterns and formatting in utility functions
Improves regex patterns for better parsing of city files and refines formatting in utility functions to ensure consistency.
Adds missing commas in function calls for clarity and maintains code style.
Enhances error handling by ensuring proper file parsing and improving readability.

Adds new hotel and room options for Amsterdam and Athens
Introduces new hotel listings and detailed room options for City Lights Inn, Grand Central Hotel, The Prestige Hotel, and Oceanview Inn in Amsterdam and Athens.
Enhances user experience by expanding accommodation choices, providing comprehensive amenities, and updating contact information.
Also includes various updates to existing hotel details, ensuring accuracy and relevance for users seeking lodging options in these cities.

Updates homestay listings for Amsterdam and Athens
Refines host information and enhances guest policies for improved user experience.
Changes include updates to host details, languages, curfews, and availability, ensuring listings accurately reflect the current offerings.
Additionally, adjusts guest policies to promote inclusivity and better accommodate various traveler needs.
This aims to enhance the quality and attractiveness of the listings.

Remove unused attraction data for various cities
Eliminates outdated and unnecessary attraction data files for cities including Amsterdam, Athens, Auckland, Bali, Bangkok, Barcelona, Berlin, Bermuda, and Boston.
This cleanup improves project maintainability and reduces clutter in the codebase.

Implements variable name consistency and adds options
Refactors variable naming conventions across multiple scripts to ensure consistency by removing periods from country names.
Adds options for additional data types in the data deletion script, enhancing the script’s functionality for managing generated data.
Improves code readability and maintainability.

Fixes missing newline at end of file in format-utils
Ensures proper formatting by adding a newline at the end of the file.
This change improves consistency and prevents potential issues with file handling in various editors and tools.

Fixes newline omission at end of data-generator file
Adds a newline at the end of the data-generator.mjs file to adhere to coding standards and improve file consistency.
Ensuring proper file termination can prevent issues in some editors and tools that expect a newline at the end of files.

Adds new attractions for multiple cities
Includes updated city identifiers and adds popular attractions for Auckland, Bali, Berlin, Boston, Bermuda, Buenos Aires, Cape Town, Cartagena, Charleston, Copenhagen, Dublin, Florence, Helsinki, Hong Kong, Lisbon, Los Angeles, Montreal, Oslo, Quebec City, Roatan, San Juan, Santiago, Santorini, Seattle, Shanghai, Singapore, Tampa, Toronto, Vancouver, and others.
This enhancement improves the application's offerings by expanding the list of attractions, making it more comprehensive and user-friendly for travelers.
Remove AttractionTags type definition to simplify type management
Add forceConsistentCasingInFileNames option to tsconfig for improved file name consistency
Refactor BaseAttraction interface to remove AttractionTags type and use string array for tags
Add Washington DC attractions and remove Yokohama attractions; introduce Zurich attractions
Refactor city attractions generation to standardize city name formatting and improve file naming consistency
Add capitalize function for improved string formatting
Export cityAttractions as attractionAddresses for improved accessibility
Reorder cityFiles array for improved organization and consistency
Enhance city attractions generation by normalizing city names and integrating real attraction data sources
Refactor city name formatting to use formatKebebToTitleCase function across multiple scripts
Add formatKebebToTitleCase function for kebab-case to title case conversion
Add city attractions integration for dynamic city titles
Implement code changes to enhance functionality and improve performance

Adds vessel information to booking confirmation page
Integrates vessel details into the booking confirmation page, enhancing user experience by displaying relevant cruise vessel information such as name, type, capacity, and key amenities.
Implements a new tab for vessel details and incorporates conditional rendering for vessel information based on booking data.
Improves overall navigation by allowing users to view vessel specifics alongside booking and crew details.
Adds Cruise Vessels page component with initial content structure
Refactors file-utils.mjs for consistency and adds formatting functions for kebab and title cases
Adds City Vessel Generator script for creating and managing vessel data files
Refactors documentation in City Cruise Generator script for clarity and completeness
Adds cruise category selection and imports formatting utility

Enhances cruise and vessel type definitions
Updates the 'BaseCruise' interface to include new cruise categories, improving the specificity of cruise offerings.
Refines the 'Vessels' interface by introducing a separate 'CruiseShipType' type, allowing for more detailed classifications of vessels.
These changes enhance the overall structure and clarity of service interfaces, supporting future feature development.
Adds travel date generation function and refines form submission handling
Adds form component with context and hooks for improved form handling
Adds Booking Confirmation page with crew member filtering and pagination
Implements booking form for cruise selection with validation and package options

Enhances homepage layout and content for clarity
Improves the homepage by updating feature titles and descriptions for better engagement and clarity.
Adds responsive design elements to optimize the display for small and medium screens. Integrates an image component for a more visually appealing layout.
Refines the messaging to emphasize luxury and exploration, ensuring a cohesive narrative that aligns with the brand's identity.

Adds initial Book Your Trip page component
Introduces a new page for booking trips, featuring a header and a placeholder for future booking forms.
This sets the foundation for trip exploration and booking functionalities, enhancing user experience for trip planning.

Improves class management for restaurant hours display
Enhances the class assignment for the restaurant hours component by adding a default class of "m-0".
This change ensures consistent styling while maintaining dynamic class assignment based on the current day and dark mode settings.

Refactors cruise destination filtering and presentation
Updates the filtering logic to use predefined cruise departure locations, enhancing clarity and efficiency.
Modifies the display of cruise information to include city and country in the title for better user context.
Introduces a Card component for improved UI consistency and structure in the layout.
This change aims to streamline user navigation and improve the overall presentation of cruise options.

Refactors imports for crew member utilities
Updates the import statements in the crew members page to streamline the code structure.
Moves the import of `getRoleDescription` to a more appropriate module, enhancing code organization and maintainability.
This change aims to facilitate easier updates and reduce dependencies on utility functions.

Adds city information retrieval function
Introduces a new function to retrieve city information based on the city name from the predefined cruise departure locations.
Enhances the utility of the codebase by enabling easy access to city data, improving overall functionality for related features.

Removes role description function for crew members
Eliminates the extensive role description function for crew members to streamline the codebase.
This change reduces complexity and enhances maintainability by removing hardcoded descriptions that may no longer align with current role definitions or requirements. Future role information can be managed more dynamically or through separate documentation as needed.

Adds city information display to restaurant page
Includes city-related details such as subtitle, quote, and additional info on the restaurants page. This enhances user experience by providing more context about the dining options in the selected city.

Adds new commands for deleting various files
Introduces new scripts for deleting crew members, cruise files, restaurant menu files, and restaurant testimonials files.
These additions streamline file management by providing dedicated commands for cleanup tasks, enhancing overall system efficiency.

Refactors Amsterdam cruises data structure for consistency
Standardizes the format of cruise details, improving readability and maintainability.
Updates location data and itinerary descriptions to ensure uniformity across multiple cruise entries, enhancing clarity for future developers.
Addresses inconsistencies in object notation and enhances the organization of cruise information.

Refactors testimonial data structure for consistency
Updates the testimonial data format to use consistent object syntax across all entries.
This change enhances readability and maintainability of the code, ensuring a uniform structure for future updates.
No functional changes were made to the testimonial content itself.

Refactors Amsterdam Amstel Chophouse menu structure
Updates the menu data structure for the Amsterdam Amstel Chophouse to use consistent object notation for properties.
This change enhances readability and maintainability of the menu items by standardizing the format across all categories and items.
No functional changes are introduced, but it improves the codebase for future enhancements.

Removes redundant crew member entries for Amsterdam team
Streamlines the crew member list by removing outdated and redundant entries from the Amsterdam team.
This change enhances maintainability and clarity of the codebase, ensuring only relevant team members are included.
Fix syntax errors by adding missing commas in various scripts

Adds new cruise itineraries and updates existing details
Introduces several new cruise itineraries departing from Amsterdam, enhancing the diversity of options available to travelers.
Updates include improved descriptions, adjustments to pricing, and detailed itineraries with time at sea and on land.
Additionally, introduces new contact personnel for the cruises, ensuring better customer support and engagement.
These changes aim to provide a richer experience for users and attract a wider audience to the cruise offerings.

Adds new testimonials for Amstel Chophouse and Canal Farm Table
Introduces a comprehensive set of testimonials for Amstel Chophouse and Canal Farm Table, enhancing the dining experience narrative for users.
Removes outdated testimonials for Amsterdam Bar & Kitchen, Amsterdam Brasserie, Amsterdam House, and Anne Frank Saloon to streamline content.
Improves user engagement by providing fresh, appealing reviews that reflect current offerings and guest experiences.

Adds Atlantic Charcuterie menu and removes Atlantic Room menu
Introduces a comprehensive menu for the Atlantic Charcuterie, featuring various categories and detailed item descriptions, enhancing the dining experience.
Removes the existing Atlantic Room menu to streamline offerings and focus on the new charcuterie concept.

Removes obsolete menu data for Boston restaurants
Deletes menu data files for Beacon Smokehouse and Boston Chophouse, streamlining the project by eliminating outdated content. This change helps maintain an up-to-date and relevant codebase for restaurant menus.

Updates menu items and descriptions for Bermuda restaurant
Refines the menu structure by updating item names, prices, and descriptions to enhance clarity and appeal.
Replaces old dishes with new ones that reflect modern culinary trends while maintaining a focus on quality and local ingredients.
Improves the overall dining experience by offering a more diverse and enticing menu selection.

Adds menu data for Alexanderplatz Atelier; removes Bavarian Pizzeria menu
Introduces a new menu data structure for the Alexanderplatz Atelier, showcasing a diverse selection of dishes and drinks, while enhancing customer experience with detailed item descriptions and dietary information.
Removes the existing Bavarian Pizzeria menu to streamline offerings and focus on the new dining experience.

Adds new restaurant menu data for Barcelona locations
Introduces comprehensive menu data for two Barcelona restaurants, Barcelona Ramen-Ya and Barri Gòtic Barbecue.
This addition enhances the culinary offerings available in the application, providing detailed descriptions, pricing, and dietary information for each dish, thereby improving user experience and enabling better dining choices.
No related issues or tickets.

Adds Blue Fine Dining menu and removes Blue Harvest menu
Introduces a comprehensive menu for Blue Fine Dining in Bangkok, featuring a diverse selection of dishes across multiple categories.
Removes the outdated Blue Harvest menu to streamline offerings and enhance user experience.

Adds menu data for Blue Atelier and removes Blue Barbecue
Introduces a new menu for the Blue Atelier restaurant, featuring a comprehensive selection of dishes across multiple categories, enhancing the dining experience with detailed descriptions and dietary information.
Removes the previous Blue Barbecue menu, streamlining the restaurant offerings to focus on the Blue Atelier's culinary theme.
This change ensures a more cohesive menu presentation and aligns with the current dining strategy.

Removes Auckland cafe and provisions menu files
Deletes the Auckland cafe and provisions menu files to streamline codebase and remove outdated or redundant data.
This change enhances maintainability by eliminating unused components, allowing for a more efficient and cleaner project structure.

Adds new menu data for Blue Project in Athens
Introduces a comprehensive menu for the Blue Project restaurant in Athens, replacing the previous Ristorante menu. This update enhances the dining experience by offering a diverse selection of Italian-inspired dishes across various categories, including main courses, appetizers, desserts, and drinks, to cater to a wider range of preferences and dietary requirements.

Adds Amstel Chophouse menu data for Amsterdam
Introduces a comprehensive menu data set for Amstel Chophouse, featuring detailed descriptions, categories, and items, enhancing the restaurant's offerings for customer engagement.
Removes the outdated Amsterdam Bar & Kitchen menu data to streamline the codebase and focus on current menu options.
This update improves the culinary representation of the restaurant and provides a richer dining experience.

Updates Amsterdam team members with new roles and bios
Replaces existing crew member data with updated entries for the Amsterdam team, enhancing diversity and reflecting current staffing.
Adds new members with detailed roles, experiences, and language proficiencies to improve the team's representation and operational capabilities.
Removes outdated entries to maintain relevance and accuracy in crew member information.

Refactors file deletion scripts for improved organization
Consolidates and reorganizes the deletion scripts for crew members and restaurant menu files into a more coherent structure.
Removes redundant scripts and unifies the logic to streamline operations, enhancing maintainability and clarity.
Additionally, updates import paths and improves user interaction for file deletions, promoting a better user experience.
Fixes #123
Add geographic data for additional cities and their coordinates

Enhance transportation services by adding new aircraft, vehicles, and yachts to the selection guide. Updated aircraft options include Cessna Citation M2, Cirrus Vision SF50, Gulfstream G280, and more. Expanded vehicle offerings feature luxury models like Bentley Flying Spur, Rolls-Royce Cullinan, and armored vehicles. Introduced new yacht options such as Celestial Legacy and Quantum Blue, along with detailed amenities and features for each category.

Add detailed FAQs addressing group travel, sustainable practices, cultural immersion, family services, luggage transfers, dietary needs, and connectivity options to enhance user support and engagement.
Refactor contact department descriptions for clarity and engagement
Implement code changes to enhance functionality and improve performance
Add testimonials for aviation, general, ground transportation, homestay, and yacht services to enhance user engagement and showcase diverse client experiences.

Enhance cultural highlights for homestay destinations in India, Japan, Italy, Vietnam, Morocco, and Nepal with detailed activities and experiences, including subtitles for each location to enrich user engagement and provide a more immersive travel narrative.
Add FAQs for special occasions, loyalty rewards, language support, travel insurance, and property previews
Refactor homestay interfaces to improve structure and type safety
Add imports for TourCategory and react-icons to enhance tour category representation
Enhance tour category descriptions for improved clarity and engagement

Adds Location type with detailed attributes for enhanced geographical context
Adds country information to homestay destinations for improved clarity and organization
Adds detailed host information for homestay locations in India, Japan, Italy, and Vietnam to enhance cultural immersion for guests
Adds new homestay locations in India, Japan, Italy, and Vietnam with detailed descriptions
Make buttons in PrivateAviation and YachtCharters components navigate to contact information
